Though I have been unable to collate this valuable MS. from the original text,l have, nevertheless-thanks to the kindness of Professor Francesco de Bofarull, the Archivist General-been able to obtain photographs of the entire 70 pages, and,with the exception of the Harleian MS. at the British Museum, I feel sure there is no earlier version. I have the support of several authorities in placing this Codex in the first half of the 13th century, and it thus becomes a work of peculiar valuc from a textual point of view.
